column1: Table 7: Most popular name for baby boys, by Local Authority1, 2018

1 Births where the usual residence of mother was outside of England and Wales have been excluded from these figures. Of the 337,584 baby boys in the 2018 dataset, 78 were excluded because they were born to non-residents of England and Wales.
2 Figures are based on geography boundaries as of May 2019.
3 Areas where the top name had a count of 2 or less have been redacted using S40 of the Freedom of Information Act in order to protect the confidentiality of individuals.
